-- Venture Capital Bank May Spend at Least $250 Million in Turkey
-- B y   E r c a n   E r s o y
-- 2012-02-06T16:02:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-06/venture-capital-bank-may-spend-at-least-250-million-in-turkey.html
Venture Capital  Bank BSC of Bahrain
will spend at least $250 million in Turkey over the next five
years, said chief executive Abdullatif Mohamed Janahi.  Venture Capital, which is a Shariah-compliant private
equity firm, is looking at the health, consumer and real estate
industries in Turkey, Janahi said in an interview in Istanbul
today.  He spoke after Venture Capital and Bank Alkhair BSC of
Bahrain agreed today to pay about $100 million for 65 percent of
Goknur Gida, a Turkish fruit juice maker that sells products to
companies including Pepsi Co and  Coca-Cola Co. (KO)   To contact the reporter on this story:
Ercan Ersoy in Istanbul at 
